tbread)%20with%20onions%20and%20%3Cem%3Episyun%20loon%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F187720%2Futtarakhand-flavoured-salt-pisi-loon-traditional-food-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epahadi%20%3C%2Fem%3Esalt%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehand%20grounded%20on%20%3Cem%3Esilbatta%3C%2Fem%3E%20(traditional%20grinding%20stone).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20offered%20me%20the%20%3Cem%3Echapati%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20salt%20made%20with%20garlic%20and%20green%20chillies.%20It%20was%20extremely%20tasty.%20I%20also%20ate%20%3Cem%3Ekakdi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Armenian%20cucumber)%20with%20this%20salt.%20Then%2C%20I%20realised%20it%20is%20this%20salt%20that%20makes%20%3Cem%3Epahadi%20%3C%2Fem%3Efood%20so%20flavoursome.%20I%20recalled%20how%20my%20mother%20would%20pack%20this%20salt%20whenever%20I%20went%20out%20of%20town%20for%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20realised%20no%20one%20had%20thought%20of%20commercialising%20this%20salt%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20relishing%20the%20meal%2C%20Sandeep%20also%20got%20a%20glimpse%20into%20the%20harsh%20lives%20of%20hill%20women.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20women%20were%20working%20under%20the%20MGNREGA%20scheme%20as%20labourers%20and%20their%20job%20was%20to%20dig%20ground%20and%20lift%20boulders%20%E2%80%94%20all%20for%20a%20daily%20wage%20of%20Rs%20270.%20The%20work%20was%20said%20to%20guarantee%20100%20days%20of%20employment%20in%20a%20year%20but%20the%20system%20was%20corrupt%20at%20the%20village%20level.%20There%20was%20no%20surety%20on%20timely%20payments%20and%20number%20of%20working%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FHimFla-2-1716968175.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22HimFl